rComments: The worst teacher I've ever had. She seems nice but she does everything to make the course impossible for the students. She is unclear in her explanations, does nothing but put YouTube videos and demands that we be able to understand. The evaluations are too strict. If you care about your mental health, never take a class with her.
She's really nice, but she's very confusing when giving instructions about her tests. It should be an extremely easy class but the lack of clarity makes you work twice as hard for a simple project.

The worst professor ever. She seems like a nice lady but honestly cannot teach at all. She is so unclear about every assignment and the assignments hardly make sense. She is confusing and made the class 10000x harder than it needed to be. The worst!!!

Should not be teaching in English but she's a nice woman. This class though was pretty bad. We're supposed to have 2 lectures a week and a tutorial but we had 5 classes the entire semester and she posts youtube videos and wordy readings as her matieral. She tries though - she's kind.

By far the worst prof I have ever had in my years at Uni. Her assignments were so unclear we had 1h group discussions on Zoom between students to make sure we all understood what she wanted. Her classes were 50% watching videos she found online and 50% having a discussion about them in breakout rooms. Presented 2-3 PowerPoints all semester... Avoid
She should not be teaching in English, period. Communication is extremely difficult and expectations are very unclear. Terrible teacher, learned nothing.
Seems like a nice lady, but has no business teaching a graduate course in English. She tries to be helpful, but it doesn't make up for her poor communication/teaching. Avoid at all costs

Elle enseigne comme si les étudiants connaissaient déjà la matière, aucune explication n'est fournie. Elle n'explique pas la raison pour laquelle on utilise une analyse en particulier. Donc, quand vient le temps d'appliquer ce qui a été vu en classe  NÉAN ! Elle n'est d'une aucune aide. Elle se dit disponible, mais en réalité, elle ne l'est pas.
